  <h1>Privacy Policy for Number Quest</h1>

  <p class="effective-date">Effective Date: June 10, 2026</p>

  <p>
    Number Quest is an educational math game designed for children and families.
    This Privacy Policy explains how the app handles information.
  </p>

  <h2>Developer</h2>

  <p>
    Number Quest is developed by Sevil Erdal.
  </p>

  <p>
    For privacy questions, you can contact:
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Email:</strong>
    <a href="mailto:sevil.ozgur.erdal@gmail.com">sevil.ozgur.erdal@gmail.com</a>
  </p>

  <h2>Summary</h2>

  <p>
    Number Quest is designed to be privacy-friendly.
  </p>

  <p>
    The app does not collect, store, sell, or share personal information.
  </p>

  <p>The app does not use:</p>

  <ul>
    <li>third-party analytics SDKs</li>
    <li>advertising SDKs</li>
    <li>personalized ads</li>
    <li>user accounts</li>
    <li>social login</li>
    <li>location tracking</li>
    <li>camera access</li>
    <li>microphone access</li>
    <li>contact access</li>
    <li>push notifications</li>
    <li>in-app chat or messaging</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Information We Collect</h2>

  <p>
    Number Quest does not collect personal information from users.
  </p>

  <p>
    The app does not ask children or parents to enter names, email addresses,
    phone numbers, photos, location, school information, or any other personal details.
  </p>

  <h2>Children’s Privacy</h2>

  <p>
    Number Quest is intended to be suitable for children.
  </p>

  <p>
    We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. The app does not
    include account creation, online profiles, chat features, behavioral advertising,
    or third-party tracking.
  </p>

  <p>
    If you believe that personal information has been provided to us by mistake,
    please contact us at:
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Email:</strong>
    <a href="mailto:sevil.ozgur.erdal@gmail.com">sevil.ozgur.erdal@gmail.com</a>
  </p>

  <p>
    We will take reasonable steps to delete such information if it exists.
  </p>

  <h2>Local Game Progress</h2>

  <p>
    Number Quest may save basic gameplay progress locally on the user’s device, such as:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>completed levels</li>
    <li>unlocked levels</li>
    <li>stars or scores</li>
    <li>basic progress settings</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    This information stays on the device and is not sent to us or to third parties.
  </p>

  <p>
    If the app is deleted from the device, this local progress may also be deleted.
  </p>

  <h2>Advertising</h2>

  <p>
    Number Quest does not show ads.
  </p>

  <p>
    The app does not use advertising networks, personalized advertising,
    behavioral advertising, or advertising identifiers.
  </p>

  <h2>Analytics</h2>

  <p>
    Number Quest does not use third-party analytics tools.
  </p>

  <p>
    We do not track users across apps or websites.
  </p>

  <h2>Internet and Online Features</h2>

  <p>
    The current version of Number Quest does not require users to create an account
    or connect to an online service to play.
  </p>

  <p>
    The app is designed to work without collecting personal data.
  </p>

  <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>

  <p>
    Number Quest does not currently use third-party services that collect user data.
  </p>

  <p>
    If this changes in a future version, this Privacy Policy will be updated before
    those features are released.
  </p>

  <h2>Data Sharing</h2>

  <p>
    We do not sell, rent, trade, or share users’ personal information.
  </p>

  <p>
    Because Number Quest does not collect personal information, there is no personal
    information to share.
  </p>

  <h2>Data Security</h2>

  <p>
    Number Quest is designed to minimize privacy risk by not collecting personal information.
  </p>

  <p>
    Any gameplay progress saved by the app is stored locally on the device.
  </p>

  <h2>Parent and Guardian Rights</h2>

  <p>
    Parents or guardians may contact us with privacy questions at:
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Email:</strong>
    <a href="mailto:sevil.ozgur.erdal@gmail.com">sevil.ozgur.erdal@gmail.com</a>
  </p>

  <p>
    Because Number Quest does not collect personal information, we usually will not
    have any user data to access, change, or delete.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>

  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy if the app changes.
  </p>

  <p>
    If we add features such as analytics, ads, accounts, online services, or any feature
    that collects information, we will update this Privacy Policy to explain what changes
    and why.
  </p>

  <p>
    The updated policy will be posted with a new effective date.
  </p>

